headline: Trimble’s Q2 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: Trimble’s results for Q2 were driven by continued adoption of its bundled software and cloud-based solutions across construction and logistics. headline: 3 Reasons to Sell TRMB and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Trimble has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 9.1%. The stock now trades at $84.37, marking a 14.5% gain. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
